Opcode [8 Bits] Operand1 [8 Bits] Operand2 [8 Bits] Operand3 [8 Bits]

OPC → Opcode
OPR → Operand

Registers:                   (Hex Index)
PC → Program Counter        
A → General Purpose Register     [0x1]
B → General Purpose Register     [0x2]
C → General Purpose Register     [0x3]
D → General Purpose Register     [0x4]
E → General Purpose Register     [0x5]
TMP → Temporary Storage Register [0x6]

Instruction Set Architecture:

  (Opcode)

MOV: (0x00) → Move Value OPR2 into Register Index OPR1
   Operand 1: (Register Index)
   Operand 2: (Hex Value)

JMP: (0x01) → Change PC value to OPR1
   Operand 1: (Hex Value)

Arithmetic Instructions:

ADD: (0x02) → Add Value OPR2 to value of Register Index OPR1 → Stored back into Reg Index OPR1
   Operand 1: (Register Index)
   Operand 2: (Hex Value)

SUB: (0x02) → Subtract Value OPR2 from value of Register Index OPR1 → Stored back into Reg Index OPR1
   Operand 1: (Register Index)
   Operand 2: (Hex Value)

MUL: (0x02) → Multiply Value OPR2 with value of Register Index OPR1 → Stored back into Reg Index OPR1
   Operand 1: (Register Index)
   Operand 2: (Hex Value)

DIV: (0x02) → Divide Value of Register Index OPR1 from value OPR2 OPR1 → Stored back into Reg Index OPR1
   Operand 1: (Register Index)
   Operand 2: (Hex Value)


